title: Did you congratulate the Girl Scout Amy Connie Barrett on Twitter?
subtitle: The organization has written headlines for more than just their own biscuits sales.
author: Madison Dapcevich
vclaim: The Girl Scouts of the United States of America participated in the tweet, which was now cancelled on 28 October 2020, congratulating Barrett on becoming "the fifth woman appointed to the Supreme Court since its establishment in 1789."
